<div class="user-guide">
    <img class="user-guide-img" src="how_to_one.png" alt="Picture of how-to"/>
    <h4 style="margin-top: 4vh; text-align: center;">In order to start using Felix, - follow the steps below:</h4>
    <br>

    <table>
        <tr class="vMiddlehLeft">
            <td style="width: 25vh;"><h6>1. Add new system<h6></td>
            <td><p>Add new system for XREF analysis. Fill all the required data: system name, 
                path to local source files, propath, entry points and database configuration data.</p></td>
        </tr>
        
        <tr class="vMiddlehLeft">
            <td><h6>2. Select from available systems<h6></td>
            <td><p>Section "Available systems" indicates systems available for Xref analysis.
                <br><img src="errorButton.png"/> button apprears if any compilation errors occurr during Xref compilation process. 
                    You can click on the button to see list of errors.</p></td>
        </tr>

        <tr class="vMiddlehLeft">
            <td><h6>3. Choose category<h6></td>
            <td><p>Choose a category of the element you are searching: file, database field or files marked as unused.</p></td>
        </tr>

        <tr class="vMiddlehLeft">
            <td><h6>4. Insert name<h6></td>
            <td><p>Insert name of the element you are searching. The more correct and specific name 
                   you enter, the better search results you get.</p></td>
        </tr>

        <tr class="vMiddlehLeft">
            <td><h6>5. Choose a type<h6></td>
            <td><p>Choose a type of the element you are searching: procedure, class, include, 
                   database field ("access" or "update" ...), index or files marked as unused.</p></td>
        </tr>

        <tr class="vMiddlehLeft">
            <td><h6>6. Click report or tree view button<h6></td>
            <td><p>Felix XREF analyser outputs Report or Tree view:
            "Report" shows all ABL elements which are using the searched element 
            "Tree View" shows all ABL elements that searched element is using and all ABL 
            elements which are used by seached element. </p></td>
        </tr>
    </table>

